On February 4, 2022, the Chief Sanitary Doctor of Kostanay Region, Kazakhstan, permitted the activities of:
- preschool institutions (duty groups) with no more than 25 people in a group;
- specialized organizations, boarding schools for children with special educational needs (including orphans), boarding schools of a general type, boarding schools for gifted children;
- allow full-time education for first-year students of colleges and universities from the second semester;
- allow the work of children's sections, clubs, electives with the number of students in groups of no more than 15 people, with a work schedule from 9 A.M. to 8 P.M. and suspension of activities on Sundays and holidays.
From the fourth quarter of the 2020-2021 academic year:
- education in the traditional format in urban and rural schools with a contingent of up to 300 students, with the number of children in classes of no more than 25 people;
- education in a combined format in other general education schools for students of all grades, with the number of children in classes no more than 25 people;
- individual training of students outside school hours in groups of no more than 15 people by decision of the administration of the educational organization.

