In Kazakhstan, from March 25, 2021 
- in all regions of the republic: teaching in a traditional format in urban and rural schools with a contingent of up to 300 students, with a number of children in classes of no more than 25 people;  
- individual teaching of students after school hours in groups of no more than 15 people by decision of the administration of the educational organization;  
- in regions located in low and moderate-risk zones (green and yellow zones), teaching in a combined format in general education schools for students of all grades, with the number of children in classes no more than 25 people; 
- in regions located in the high-risk zone (red zone):  teaching in a combined format in general education schools for students of preschool classes, from grades 1 to 5 inclusive, in international schools - from grades 1 to 7 inclusive, with the number of children in classes no more than 25 people;  teaching in a combined format for 6 days of the week for graduation classes (grades 9, 11 (12)): 70% of subjects in the regular mode, 30% - in distance (no more than 15 people in a class, training according to the principle "1 grade - 1 cabinet ", compliance with sanitary-disinfection and mask regimes)

