According to the decree of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Kostanay region (Kazakhstan), it is forbidden to go outside from 10:00 p.m. till 06:00 a.m. starting from April 17, 2020. 
Exit is permitted in the following cases:
- going to work;
- seeking medical help;
- purchase of food products, medicines and medical products in pharmacies and shops close to the place of residence or work;
- dog walking within a radius of no more than 500 meters from the place of residence;
- visiting the nearest gas station from the place of residence to purchase fuel;
- a walk in the yard;
- visiting summer cottages.

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 6 dated on 13th April 2020, the entry into the territory of the region from other regions of all persons and vehicles is prohibited, with the exception of:
- residents of the Almaty region returning from foreign countries;
- persons and vehicles for the carriage of goods, including transit

