The order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 8 dated on 28th April 2020 requires Akims of districts and cities, rural districts, the Police Department and other involved services of the Almaty region to:

- ensure the allocation of vehicles for the transport of medical workers from/to quarantine hospitals and places of residence;

- secure permanent drivers and keep them under medical supervision.

The Main Sanitary Doctor of East Kazakhstan region, starting from November 15, 2021, decrees:
Individuals to provide:

1) compliance with the mask regime:

Wearing medical or fabric masks is mandatory for the population:

- outdoors (outdoors, outside the house), in public places, including at bus stops;

- in closed premises intended for visiting, servicing and recreation of the population, as well as facilities whose activities are permitted;

- in public transport, including taxis;

- healthy persons, when providing assistance to a person with suspicion, or a patient with a coronavirus infection COVID-19;

- persons who have symptoms of the disease similar to coronavirus infection, patients with symptoms of coronavirus infection (fever, shortness of breath or cough), or who have positive results of PCR or rapid testing.

Medical or fabric masks should be worn correctly: the mask should cover the nose, mouth and chin, fit snugly to the face at the edges and be fixed; during a conversation, the mask should not be moved to the chin and removed, as well as tied on the arm or neck.

