By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 4 dated on 30th March 2020, the movement of personal vehicles and people across the territory of the Almaty region, including from the quarantine zone of Almaty, on the border with the East Kazakhstan and Zhambyl regions is restricted, with the exception of:

1) persons and vehicles for the carriage of goods, delivery services, as well as specialized vehicles necessary to ensure the life of the region, medical organizations, government and law enforcement agencies, communications services and other organizations with the permission of the local executive body;
2) persons for medical reasons, accompanied by no more than two people, with the following documents:
- the conclusion of the medical consulting commission of the territorial outpatient organization to confirm the diagnosis and urgency of treatment, in accordance with the form 035-1/y, approved by order of the Acting Minister of Health of the Republic of Kazakhstan dated November 23, 2010 №907 "On approval of forms of primary medical documentation of healthcare organizations ";
- an invitation letter from a medical organization located in the quarantine zone with an indication of the diagnosis and confirmation of urgency, signed by the first head and certified by the official seal.

