From November 2, 2020, railway and airline movements from and to Ust-Kamenogorsk, Kazakhstan, will be restricted. In order to stabilize the epidemiological situation in the region, the Chairman of the Interdepartmental Commission instructed to take a number of restrictive measures:
- from November 2 of this year reduce air traffic for entry and exit from Ust-Kamenogorsk:
to / from Nur-Sultan - from 17 to 7 flights per week;
to/from Almaty – from 14 to 7 flights per week;
to / from Shymkent - from 2 to 1 flight per week.
- from November 2 of this year to reduce the railway communication on the routes Nur-Sultan-Ust-Kamenogorsk from 3 to 1 time per week, Almaty - Ust-Kamenogorsk from 7 to 3 times per week;

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty City dated 26th March 2020, a restriction is introduced on the exit of citizens from their places of residence, with the exception of the following cases:

· Purchasing food and basic necessities and medicines;
· Going to work;
· Seeking medical help.

According to the Chief Sanitary Doctor of Karaganda region, starting April 18, 2020, prohibit movement, including using personal vehicles, unless absolutely necessary, except in the following cases:

- movement from place of residence to place of work and back for employees of organizations, according to permitted types of activity (if information is available in the information system of the Rapid Response Center);

- the purchase of food products, medicines and medical products in stores and pharmacies in the immediate vicinity of the place of residence or work, but within a radius of no more than 1.5 km (if any);

- grazing livestock in compliance with the established veterinary and sanitary standards for keeping animals.

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 6 dated on 13th April 2020, the quarantine was introduced in Almaty Region. The regime and timing of quarantine measures may be changed in accordance with the changing situation on the spread of COVID-19. UPDATE: By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region (Kazakhstan) № 16 dated on 12th June 2020:
- the quarantine regime in the Almaty region will be continued;
- increased quarantine measures will be introduced on the territory of districts and cities of the Almaty region with an unfavorable epidemiological situation;
- the regime and terms of quarantine may be changed in accordance with the change in the situation on the spread of the coronavirus infection "COVID-19".

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 6 dated on 13th April 2020, the quarantine was introduced in Almaty Region. The regime and timing of quarantine measures may be changed in accordance with the changing situation on the spread of COVID-19. UPDATE: By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 18 dated on 23rd April 2020, Almaty region will strengthen quarantine measures to prevent spread of COVID-19, including the following changes:

- It is prohibited to hold meetings, conferences, forums, seminars and other events of mass gatherings;
- operation of public catering facilities, with the capacity of more than 30 seats, and in open summer areas with the capacity of more than 50 seats will be suspended;
- shopping and entertainment centers, religious facilities, educational centers, art clubs, places of children's leisure and additional training, correctional rooms for children and preschool organizations will be closed.
- Planned hospitalization and primary health care organizations' preventive works, screening (professional examinations), planned dental care, medical rehabilitation had been put on hold. The exceptions are: routine immunization of the population, medical manipulations for health reasons, admission and screening of pregnant women.

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 8 dated on 28th April 2020, starting from 28th April 2020, Akims of districts and cities of the region, the Department of Entrepreneurship and Industrial and Innovative Development of the Almaty Region and the NPP "Atameken" of the region are required to ensure:

1) the creation of an interdepartmental commission to assess the readiness of facilities approved for the phased removal of restrictions, for compliance with the requirements, recommendations for activities during the quarantine period with the issuance of an act of readiness in accordance with Appendix No. 1, and in case of non-compliance, recommendations for eliminating the identified comments and violations in accordance with Appendix No. 2 for each of them on an individual basis;

2) constant monitoring according to the schedule by the interdepartmental commission of objects that have received an act of readiness to lift restrictions. If violations are detected, take measures in accordance with the legislation of the Republic of Kazakhstan with the revocation of the activity permit;

3) carrying out outreach work through information channels, mass media, videoconferences with the participation of specialized associations, posting the necessary information on official web resources and social networks.

On May 11, 2020,  Prime minister of Kazakhstan announced that the following documents remain valid past the expiration date if it is the date within the period of the state of emergency and 60 days after it:
1) identity documents specified in article 6 of the Law of the Republic of Kazakhstan "On identity documents";
2) driving licenses, including temporary ones and certificates of compulsory technical inspection;
3) permits for the acquisition, storage and carrying of civilian and service weapons and cartridges for them.
The policy is to be enforced retroactively, from March 16 and last until July 9.

By the order of the Chief Sanitary Doctor of the Almaty Region № 6 dated on 13th April 2020, the Department of Internal Policy of the region and the mass media have to:

1) strengthen outreach work with an emphasis on the prevention of coronavirus infection caused by COVID-19 at home, personal prevention measures and tactics of behavior in case of illness;

2) post reliable information for the population from official sources (coronavirus2020.kz. anti-corona.kz, official websites of the Government, the Ministry of Health and Akimats).

Following the Decree of the Deputy Chief State Sanitary Doctor of the Mangystau Region to the Department of internal policy of Mangystau region dated August 14, 2020:
1) objects whose activities are suspended and allowed should be notified through information channels;
2) official sources should post reliable information about COVID-19 and the related measures for the population;
3) spread of COVID-19 should be prevented by continuing to strengthen awareness-raising efforts.

From 28.01.2022 in West Kazakhstan
- inform the population about the restrictive measures taken through the mass media and social networks;

- develop leaflets for the public on the restrictive measures taken, including instructions for citizens on observing precautionary measures, rules of conduct on the streets during the period of restrictive measures, indicating all the necessary contacts for emergency and emergency services;

- carry out information support in the media about the measures taken to localize the foci of infection and minimize the risks of its spread among the inhabitants of the region;

