On March 29, 2022, the Chief Sanitary Doctor of Kostanay Region, Kazakhstan, announced the implementation of a differentiated approach to quarantine in secondary education, colleges, and higher educational institutions. When a case of group COVID-19 disease is registered in the 1st incubation period, isolation for home quarantine for up to 10 days is introduced for: 
- class (group) - in case more than 30% of the size of the class is infected; 
- school shift - in case more than 30% of classes in one shift are infected; - stream - in case more than 30% groups of one stream in colleges or higher education institutions are infected. Students who complete the home quarantine can return to the classes without a laboratory examination for COVID-19 by PCR or a doctor's medical opinion on the absence of medical contraindications for staying in an educational organization.

On March 16, 2020, the acting head of the administration of Baikonur city (Kazakhstan) declared that all businesses operating on the territory of the city need to observe the following practices:
 - temperature checks of employees before work; 
 - regularly use bactericidal lamps, air recirculators in working rooms;
 - perform cleaning every 2 hours using detergents and disinfectants;
 - ensure at least a five-day supply of disinfectants;
 - limit business trips and outbound vacations for employees, and control returning workers from overseas business trips and vacations from countries where COVID-19 cases have been registered;
 - employees should comply with the rules of personal and public hygiene throughout the working day, after each visit to the toilet;
 - workers should self-isolate at home for at least 14 days in case of their return from countries with COVID-19 cases.

In Pavlodar region (Kazakhstan), starting March 19, 2020, the Chief Sanitary Doctor orders restrictions on the functioning of shopping facilities (shopping centres, hypermarkets, food markets, supermarkets, minimarkets, convenience stores, other retail outlets). To strengthen sanitary and disinfection measures, in particular:
- workday 10 am till 6 pm; 
- baked goods only to be sold in a packaged form;
- sales of packaged food products, with the exception of vegetables and fruits;
- enhanced disinfection regime: every 3 hours, with special disinfectants: treat tables, chairs, escalator handrails, stairs, doors, elevators and floors;
