By the order of the Chief sanitary doctor of the Akmola region (Kazakhstan), starting March 20, the retail facilities (shopping centres, hypermarkets, trading houses, supermarkets, minimarkets, convenience stores, others) with an area of ​​less than 2,000 s. m., as well as food markets, are to strengthen sanitary safety measures:
 - only sell packaged food products including bakery, except for vegetables and fruits;
 - disinfect tables, chairs, escalator handrails (if any), stairs, doors, elevators and floors every 3 hours;
 - distribute coronavirus prevention pamphlets to visitors;
 - install hand sanitizers;
 - issue disposable gloves to the staff;
 - not allowing people with symptoms (fever, cough, runny nose) to work;
 - carry out regular ventilation of facilities, disinfect air handling units, increase filtration and ventilation of premises by drawing in air from outside;
 - prevent the formation of queues of more than 5 people, observing the distance between them at least one meter;
 - disinfect the adjacent areas at least daily;
 - assign responsible employees in retail facilities, ensuring compliance with the above points.

By the order of the Chief sanitary doctor of the Akmola region (Kazakhstan), starting March 20, the catering facilities (restaurants, cafes, bars, canteens, etc.) need to:
 - restrict the number of clients to no more than 50 people at a time;
 - install hand sanitizers or provide disposable gloves;
 - disinfect door handles, handrails, tables, chairs, sinks for washing hands at the entrance to the dining room, self-service stations every 3 hours; 
 - prohibit self-service by customers in canteens on the distribution line;
 - not allow people with symptoms (fever, cough, runny nose) to work;
 - the staff are to use disposable (change every 3 hours) masks during shifts;
 - carry out regular ventilation of facilities at the end of the work shift (every 6 hours);
 - disinfect the adjacent areas at least daily;
 - staff is to provide services in disposable gloves (to be replaced at least twice a shift and in case of violation of integrity): sellers, cooks, waiters, cashiers and other employees who have direct contact with food;
 - observe the distance of at least 2 metres between the tables.

