According to the Chief Sanitary Doctor of Karaganda region in Kazakhstan, starting from May 3, The resumption of operation of subjects in the field of rendering hairdressing services, salons beauty, and cosmetic services is allowed only if the following conditions are met in compliance with sanitary and epidemiological requirements:
- before opening the facility, carry out a high-quality general cleaning of all premises (cash desks, waiting room, common room, offices, utility rooms, etc.), as well as equipment, including manicure tables and pedicure chairs using detergents and disinfectants (washing all surfaces (tables, chairs, etc.), including glazed surfaces of natural light frames (windows);
- organize activities by appointment to exclude crowds:
- treat the area adjacent to the facility with disinfectants at least 1 time per day and keep it clean;
- not provide services to visitors with respiratory symptoms;
- to check workers for symptoms of respiratory diseases, by the method of non-contact thermometry or individual medical thermometers (with a note in the log about the results), while processing the thermometers after each use with disinfectants in accordance with the instructions for use;
- suspend personnel with symptoms of SARS and influenza from work, and for persons with symptoms that do not exclude coronavirus infection (dry cough, fever, difficulty breathing, shortness of breath, etc.), ensure isolation and an immediate call for an ambulance by phone 103;

According to the Chief Sanitary Doctor of Karaganda region in Kazakhstan, starting from May 3, The resumption of operation of stores selling industrial goods (non-food shops) with a total area of up to 500 sq.m. is allowed only if the following conditions are met in compliance with sanitary and epidemiological requirements:
- before opening a store, carry out a high-quality general cleaning of all retail, warehouse, and household premises, as well as all available equipment using detergents and disinfectants (washing all surfaces, including glazed surfaces of natural light frames (windows), trade equipment;
- work schedule from 9.00 to 18.00;
- to transfer personnel not involved in the work process to the remote operating mode as much as possible;
- treat the area adjacent to the object with disinfectants at least 1 time per day and keep it clean.

